<refsect2 id="bluetooth-chooser-button-available" role="function">
<title>bluetooth_chooser_button_available ()</title>
<indexterm zone="bluetooth-chooser-button-available"><primary sortas="bluetooth_chooser_button_available">bluetooth_chooser_button_available</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="gboolean">gboolean</link>            bluetooth_chooser_button_available  (<link linkend="BluetoothChooserButton">BluetoothChooserButton</link> *button);</programlisting>
<para>
Returns whether there is a powered Bluetooth adapter.</para>
<para>
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>button</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> a <link linkend="BluetoothChooserButton"><type>BluetoothChooserButton</type></link>
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&#160;:</term><listitem><simpara> <link linkend="TRUE--CAPS"><literal>TRUE</literal></link> if there is a powered Bluetooth adapter available, and the button should be sensitive.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>

